-- Fragrance Group rises 4.4 pct on Australia spinoff plan 
-- 
-- Fri Sep 19, 2014 03:59AM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, Sept 19 (Reuters) - Shares of Singapore's Fragrance Group Ltd <FRAG.SI> rose 4.4 percent after the real estate developer said it was proposing to spin off property business based in Australia.

It is proposing to list the Australian business on the Singapore Exchange's Catalist board, used for smaller companies. The company, which has appointed SAC Capital Private Ltd as its financial adviser, said the proposed restructuring was in its preliminary stages. [ID:nSNZ4D24tc] The stock's trading volume of 1.2 million on Friday was nearly double its 30-day average.